The paper discusses the use of power-domain non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) to enhance the spectrum efficiency of BackCom system, which involves communication between backscatter nodes and a reader. This topic falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), communication (cs.COMM), and multiagent systems (cs.MA).
